case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances:
Skeletal remains were located by three children in a farm field near a creek. Forensic Entomologist advised skeletal remains are most likely that of a White of Hispanic male, height 5'3"-5'7", age 30-40 years old.  Keys to several different vehicles were located in the pants pockets. Keys appeared to belong to a ford vehicle, Chevy vehicle and misc house keys.
Decedent was wearing several layers of clothing, flannel underwear, jeans, work boots, and a watch was also located.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: Flannel underwear, blue jean pants, gray and red hunting style socks, leather work gloves, two Western Super-X buttons were also located. Appear to be buttons for a coat. Type and color were not able to be determined to the level of decomposition.
case_footwear: Leather work boots with Vibrant brand sole.
case_jewelry: Gold Bulova watch. made in the year of 1977.
case_other_items_with_body: wallet with insurance card, photo paper, picture had faded out, keys, random change
dental: Dental information / charting is currently not available
